stanford vis group socializing visualization home papers people video stanford vis group socializing visualization jeffrey heer usage observations of the vizster by heer and boyd and namevoyager by wattenberg visualizations revealed strong tendencies towards social use of the visualizations by groups of people with meaningful analytic activty conducted within a context of play abstract the immersive and compelling nature of many social visualizations arise not only from the nature and presentation of the data under consideration but also from the social interactions both implicit and explicit surrounding the use of the visualization across numerous examples the social life of visualization to borrow a phrase from wattenberg has shown to be an important factor shaping the adoption use and efficacy of a visualization an aspect often overlooked by the psychological analytic orientation of contemporary information visualization this position paper attempts a preliminary exploration of the consequences of this insight for the design of social visualizations by recasting visualization applications as not just external cognitive artifacts but social artifacts key components of this re thinking include the move from purely task based considerations to that of ludic or playful activity and an exploration of fundamental design considerations for facilitating the social dimension of visualization use materials and links pdf 201.6 kb bibtex citation citation socializing visualization jeffrey heer social visualization workshop acm chi 2006 pdf 201.6 kb rss stanford computer science
